quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  32,12,"And if only you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>could see the criminals bowing their heads before their Lord: “Our Lord, we have seen and we have heard, so send us back, that we may act righteously; we are<i class=""s"">(now) </i>certain.”"
  32,13,"And had We willed, We could have brought every soul its guidance, but the declaration from Me will come true: “I will most surely fill Hell with<i class=""s"">(the race of) </i>unseen beings{1}and human beings, both together.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jinnahwhich is the race of unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.
  32,14,"So taste, on account of how you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>forgot the meeting of this day of yours; indeed, We have forgotten you, so taste the eternal punishment on account of what you used to do."
  32,15,"The only people who<i class=""s"">(truly) </i>believe in Our signs are those who, when they are reminded of them, fall down prostrating and highly exalt their Lord with praise, and they are not arrogant."
  32,16,"Their sides shun the beds as they pray to their Lord out of fear and ardent hope, and from Our provisions to them they spend."
  32,17,"No soul knows what <span class=""h"">has been hidden<sup foot_note=""80851"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>for them{2}of comfort to the eyes—a repayment on account of what they used to do.",footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  32,18,"So, is the one who has been a believer like the one who has been defiantly disobedient? They are not equal."
  32,19,"As for those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds, for them are the Gardens of Shelter—hospitality on account of what they used to do."
  32,20,"But as for those who have defiantly disobeyed, their shelter is the Fire; every time they want to depart it, they are brought back into it, and it is said to them, “Taste the punishment of the Fire which you used to deny.”"
